text.tspan: This guy is such a downer. Jim was a Scottish guy who
really liked the idea of scamming people. He thought it
was really funny how gullible people were. Anyways,
this obviously led to his death after he scammed the
wrong person and got stabbed. Honestly, he had it
coming. But he persisted after death for the stupidest
reason possible: he wanted to scam more people!!! He
had been doing this ever since he got his high school
diploma, which is a good 61 years! He was WELL past
retirement age, and yet he still wanted to make people
lose money! Capitalism at its finest. Anyways, he didn't
get to scam any more people, but he did get a pretty
cool set of armor to spend the rest of time in. He's a
bit upset about being unable to solicit anymore, and so
he is a big pessimist all the time nowadays.
Jim
Professional pessimist
Age: 80 (soul), ~750 (armor)
Species: Soul
Alignment: Neutral
